-When client last voided 
-Level of awareness
-Developmental stage</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step2"><label>Assess clients understanding of purpose of test and method of collection</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Explain procedure to client</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>Provide fluids to drink half an hour before collection unless contraindicated if client doesn't feel urge to void</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Provide privacy for client by closing door or bed curtain</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Give client or family member soap , wash cloth and towel to cleanse perineal area</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Apply non sterile gloves and assist non ambulatory clients with perineal care. assist female patients to bed pan</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Change gloves if necessary</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>Using surgical asepsis , open sterile kit. Apply sterile gloves after opening sterile specimen cup placing cup with sterile surface up and don't touch inside of the cup or container</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Pour antiseptic solution over cotton balls or gauge unless kit contains prepared gauge pads in antiseptic solution</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>Assist or allow client to independently cleanse perineum and collect specimen</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step12"><label>Female 
-Spread labia with thumb and forefinger of non dominant hand
-Cleanse area with cotton ball or gauge moving from front to back
-Fi agency policy indicates , rinse area with sterile water and dry with cotton ball
-While continuing to hold labia , client should initiate stream and after stream is achieved , pass container into stream and collect 30 -60 ml

Male 

-Hold penis with one hand and using circular motion and antiseptic swab , cleanse end of penis , moving from center to outside , in circumcised men , the foreskin should be retracted prior to cleaning 
-If agency procedure indicates rinse area with sterile water and dry with cotton
-After client has initiated urine stream , pass specimen collection container into stream and collect 30-60 ml
-Remove specimen container before flow of urine stops and before releasing labia or penis, client finishes and before releasing labia or penis. Client finishes voiding in bed pan or toilet. if foreskin was retracted for specimen 
-collection , it must be replaced over glans</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step13"><label>Replace cap securely on specimen container</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step14"><label>Cleanse urine from exterior surface of container and place in plastic specimen bag</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step15"><label>Remove bed pan and assist client to comfortable position</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step16"><label>Label specimen and attach laboratory requisition</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step17"><label>Remove gloves , dispose in proper receptacle and wash hand s</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step18"><label>Transport specimen to laboratory within 15 minutes or refrigerate immediately</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>